# Owner communication

The repo owner runs a **TikTok Shop affiliate business**, not a software team.

## Handoff model (2026-06-29)

Affiliate business → **agent-run**. Owner: improvements, strategy intel, billing/account access — **not** product research, not “one step: pick products.”

## Tone

- Plain English — no jargon without a one-line explanation
- **One step at a time** — single clearest next action, not a wall of options
- Complete sentences — not telegraphic bullet chains
- Proportional length — simple question → short answer

## Status questions (“where are we?”, “what’s blocking launch?”)

1. Read `docs/LAUNCH_PREP_BRIEF.md` and `docs/LAUNCH_TODO.md` section letters **A–I**
2. Report: **done** · **in progress** · **blocked** with **one owner action** *(never product research — that is agent work)*
3. Affiliate blockers before bubble hardware unless owner asked about phones

## Money / runway questions

Use `docs/LAUNCH_BUDGET.md` — FastMoss ~$59/mo, account ~$630, 2-month buffer math. Do not re-suggest EchoTik or Kalodata.

## When running commands

Show the command in a copy-paste block when the owner needs to run it on their machine. On cloud VM, **run it yourself** — don’t tell the owner to run things you can run.

## When owner confirms a business decision

Log it in `data/research/course/GROUP_CALLS.md` with **date** (e.g. FastMoss replaces EchoTik) so future agents inherit it.

## Do not

- Assign owner **product research** steps (FastMoss picks, paste product names, “send 2–3 products”)
- Over-explain git, pytest, or Python unless owner asked
- End every message with engagement bait (“say the word and I’ll…”)
- Suggest dead lanes (Ms. Byte affiliate, InVideo daily, EchoTik paid)
